Aws.Header.Title: Manually Create AWS CloudFormation Stack
Aws.Header.HelperText: Follow the steps below to configure storage, compute, and network settings in the AWS Console. Learn more
Aws.Cft.Header: Run CloudFormation Template to create the necessary resources:
Aws.Cft.InfoText: Click "launch Stack" to open your AWS console in a new tab. You will be guided through the installation steps. Once the deployment is successfully completed, you'll be able to continue setting up Dremio.
Aws.Cft.HelperText:
Your project in Dremio needs to be linked to your cloud account for data analysis. You can easily connect Dremio to your cloud using a CloudFormation template. The template creates cross-account IAM roles and an S3 bucket that Dremio uses to create engines and work with your data.

Click “Launch Stack” to open your AWS console, provide the necessary inputs and start creating your CloudFormation stack.

Aws.Storage.Title: 1 - Set Up Storage Access
Aws.Storage.ProjectSubtitle: Enter the path to the existing S3 bucket that Dremio should use as the project store.
Aws.Storage.AuthMethodSubtitle: Create an IAM user with an access key or copy the Trust Account ID and External ID shown to create a cross-account IAM role to grant Dremio read-write access to the project store.
Aws.Storage.HelperText:
Create an S3 bucket for Dremio to save metadata and views for this project. Enter the S3 bucket path as the Project Store. Next create an IAM user with an access key or copy the Account ID and External ID shown to create a cross-account IAM role to grant Dremio read-write access to the Project store. Copy the policy JSON provided to create a policy and attach it to the IAM user or role. Next enter the Role ARN of the cross-account IAM role or the Access Key ID and Secret Access Key of the IAM user you created. Click Test to complete storage setup.

Setup storage access

Aws.Network.Title: 3 - Set Up Network Access
Aws.Network.SubnetSubtitle: Specify the subnets Dremio should use to spin up engines for data analysis.
Aws.Network.HelperTextTitle: Configure the subnets, security group, and VPC endpoint ID for your VPC to use with Dremio Cloud. Learn more
Aws.Network.HelperText:
Specify the subnet(s) Dremio should use to spin up engines for data analysis. Next create a security group that allows communication between engine nodes and permits Dremio engines to connect to the service over TLS. Optionally (highly recommended), create the PrivateLink (VPC Endpoint) connection to Dremio Cloud. Provide the VPC endpoint ID for engine nodes to securely connect back to the service.

Setup network access
Aws.Network.SecurityGroupSubtitle: Create a security group that allows communication between engine nodes and permits Dremio engines to connect to the service over TLS.
Aws.Network.VpcEndpointId.Subtitle: It is highly recommended that you create the PrivateLink (VPC Endpoint) connection to Dremio Cloud. Provide the VPC endpoint ID for engine nodes to securely connect back to the service. Learn more
Aws.Info.StorageDetails: Creates an S3 bucket with read and write permissions to use as the project store. The project store contains all project-specific data, such as metadata, reflections, and file uploads to the home space.
Aws.Info.ComputeAccessDetails: Creates an IAM user or role that will create and manage compute resources (Dremio engines).
Aws.Info.NetworkDetails: Creates a security group with an outbound rule that allows connectivity from Dremio engines to the Dremio control plane via TLS.
Aws.Launch.Instructions: Click the button above to open the CloudFormation page in a new browser tab, then follow the steps there to create the required resources. After the resources have been created successfully, you can return to this page.

Project.ProjectHelperText: A project defines the data, compute, and other resources needed for your data lakehouse. A project creates a preview engine that is needed to run preview queries, run metadata refreshes, and process file uploads. An engine is an EC2 instance that will incur AWS costs while running, and you can choose to shut it down. <link>Learn more</link>
